WEBVTT

00:01.235 --> 00:06.106 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Good evening. I'm
Gwen Ifill. Judy Woodruff is

00:06.139 --> 00:11.511 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
away. On the "NewsHour" tonight:
Brussels in lockdown. Belgian

00:11.545 --> 00:15.482 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
authorities remain on high alert
after a terrorist threat similar

00:15.515 --> 00:19.319 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to Paris. We look at what the
U.S. and others can and should

00:19.353 --> 00:24.258 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
be doing to stop ISIS. Also
ahead, it's Politics Monday. We

00:24.291 --> 00:27.628 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
look at how the politics of fear
is shaping the presidential

00:27.661 --> 00:32.299 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
campaign. And could tobacco
plants be key to finding a

00:32.332 --> 00:35.936 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
treatment for Ebola? KEVIN
WHALEY, Developed ZMapp: In a

00:35.969 --> 00:39.706 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
vaccine, you give a person a
protein that stimulates your own

00:39.740 --> 00:43.944 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
body to make antibodies. In this
case, we're giving antibodies

00:43.977 --> 00:46.747 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
directly to you, so your body
doesn't have to make them. GWEN

00:46.780 --> 00:49.816 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
IFILL: All that and more on
tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

00:49.850 --> 00:54.855 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
(BREAK) GWEN IFILL: Police in
Belgium charged a fourth suspect

01:05.666 --> 01:09.169 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the Paris attacks today. The
suspect was swept up in a

01:09.202 --> 01:13.240 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
24-hour dragnet, but was the
only person charged. Fifteen

01:13.273 --> 01:16.443 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
others were released. The prime
minister decided to keep

01:16.476 --> 01:19.680 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Brussels on its highest state of
alert through at least next

01:19.713 --> 01:23.417 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
week. We have a report from Emma
Murphy of Independent Television

01:23.450 --> 01:27.788 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
News in Brussels. EMMA MURPHY: A
European capital city, rush hour

01:27.821 --> 01:31.091 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Monday morning, whatever the
threat is, the government

01:31.124 --> 01:34.928 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
believed it is so serious that
much of normal life has given

01:34.962 --> 01:41.501 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
way to abnormality. Armored
vehicles patrol empty and closed

01:41.535 --> 01:44.972 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
shopping streets. There are
soldiers on most junctions, and

01:45.005 --> 01:48.809 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in such a climate all places
where lots of people can gather,

01:48.842 --> 01:53.113 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
like universities, schools and
nurseries, are shut. This isn't

01:53.146 --> 01:57.250 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a city in fear, but it is a city
in flux. MAN: It's necessary.

01:57.284 --> 02:02.189 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's necessary to have this
security because the people, I

02:02.222 --> 02:05.993 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
think, feel safer with this kind
of security. WOMAN: I feel if

02:06.026 --> 02:10.731 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the policeman -- but if I do
feel safe -- I will be glad when

02:10.764 --> 02:14.234 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm home. EMMA MURPHY: It is
affecting everyone's life,

02:14.267 --> 02:18.271 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
mainly the small everyday things
like nursery for Nathaniel, fine

02:18.305 --> 02:20.941 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for one day, but challenging if
it goes on. CHARLOTTE MCDONALD

02:20.974 --> 02:23.677 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GIBSON, Belgium: We just can't
do the simple day-to-day things

02:23.710 --> 02:26.279 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that you usually do. And there's
police everywhere, even in my

02:26.313 --> 02:29.850 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
neighborhood, which is quite
suburban, quite leafy. It's not

02:29.883 --> 02:32.386 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the sort of center of town,
but there's police on the

02:32.419 --> 02:34.588 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
streets. There's police cars
occasionally closing off the

02:34.621 --> 02:37.224 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
roads around here. So it's very
unusual. EMMA MURPHY: How long

02:37.257 --> 02:41.461 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it goes on depends in part on
this man, Salah Abdeslam. He

02:41.495 --> 02:46.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
still evades capture. He is part
of this terror threat, but the

02:46.066 --> 02:48.969 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
action of the government here
suggests there is something for

02:49.002 --> 02:52.472 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
than him for them to contend
with. GWEN IFILL: Because of

02:52.506 --> 02:55.609 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ongoing terrorist attacks around
the world, the State Department

02:55.642 --> 02:59.346 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
issued a worldwide travel alert
for U.S. citizens this evening,

02:59.379 --> 03:02.916 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
citing increased threats. It
directed Americans to -- quote

03:02.949 --> 03:06.887 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
-- "exercise vigilance in public
places or when using public

03:06.920 --> 03:10.223 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
transportation." It also
suggested avoiding large crowds,

03:10.257 --> 03:13.994 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
particularly during the holiday
season. The alert is set to

03:14.027 --> 03:17.497 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
expire in three months.
Meanwhile, in a southern suburb

03:17.531 --> 03:21.401 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of Paris, police said a street
cleaner found an explosive belt

03:21.435 --> 03:25.005 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in a pile of rubble, but without
its detonator. French President

03:25.038 --> 03:28.208 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Francois Hollande and British
Prime Minister David Cameron

03:28.241 --> 03:31.711 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
each laid a single flower
outside the Bataclan concert

03:31.745 --> 03:35.715 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
hall, where 89 people were
killed. Later, Cameron urged the

03:35.749 --> 03:39.286 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
British Parliament to join
France in the fight against the

03:39.319 --> 03:41.288 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Islamic State. DAVID CAMERON,
British Prime Minister: Later

03:41.321 --> 03:43.824 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this week, I will set out in
Parliament our comprehensive

03:43.857 --> 03:48.428 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
strategy for tackling ISIL. I
firmly support the action that

03:48.462 --> 03:52.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
President Hollande has taken to
strike ISIL in Syria and it's my

03:52.699 --> 03:56.103 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
firm conviction that Britain
should do so too. GWEN IFILL:

03:56.136 --> 03:59.005 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The French Defense Ministry said
it has launched its first

03:59.039 --> 04:02.142 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
airstrikes from the aircraft
carrier Charles de Gaulle,

04:02.175 --> 04:06.646 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
bombing Islamic State targets in
Ramadi and Mosul, Iraq. France

04:06.680 --> 04:11.251 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has already carried out strikes
against ISIS targets in Syria.

04:11.284 --> 04:14.488 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Syria was at the top of the
agenda for a meeting between

04:14.521 --> 04:17.958 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Russian President Vladimir Putin
and Iran's supreme leader,

04:17.991 --> 04:21.995 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Ayatollah Ali Khamenei. The two
leaders met in Iran. Both have

04:22.028 --> 04:25.232 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
been staunch supporters of
Syrian President Bashar

04:25.265 --> 04:30.137 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
al-Assad, and today Khamenei
criticized U.S. efforts to begin

04:30.170 --> 04:35.242 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
