Three separate groups have

05:14.748 --> 05:17.851 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
claimed responsibility for the
deadly siege that left 20

05:17.884 --> 05:22.656 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
people, plus the two attackers,
dead. In Nigeria and Cameroon,

05:22.689 --> 05:26.893 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
five suicide bombers, all girls,
killed 12 people over the

05:26.927 --> 05:30.130 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
weekend. The attacks happened at
an entry to Nigeria's

05:30.163 --> 05:33.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
northeastern city of Maiduguri,
and just across the border in

05:33.900 --> 05:37.971 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Cameroon. Police blamed Boko
Haram, the Islamic extremist

05:38.004 --> 05:42.209 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
