15:32.532 --> 15:36.269 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
territorial expansion, but the
president insists U.S.

15:36.302 --> 15:41.307 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
involvement will not include
direct ground combat. BARACK

15:46.112 --> 15:51.117 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
OBAMA: Destroying ISIL is not
only a realistic goal. We're

16:20.112 --> 16:25.117 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
going to get it done, and we're
going to pursue it with every

17:04.323 --> 17:09.328 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
aspect of American power. The
United States will continue to

17:38.357 --> 17:43.362 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
lead this global coalition. We
are intensifying our strategy on

18:12.358 --> 18:17.363 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
all fronts with local partners
on the ground. GWEN IFILL: The

18:27.907 --> 18:32.912 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
U.S. role in battling ISIS has
evolved in recent months. There

18:40.920 --> 18:45.925 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
