when he came to school. For the
"PBS NewsHour," I'm April Brown

53:58.502 --> 54:03.507 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Houston. GWEN IFILL: Finally
tonight, we return to the

54:06.610 --> 54:10.581 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
challenge of ISIS, but this time
to a look at its beginnings. The

54:10.614 --> 54:14.685 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
story is told in a new book,
"Black Flags: The Rise of ISIS."

54:14.718 --> 54:18.322 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Author Joby Warrick has covered
national security and the Middle

54:18.355 --> 54:21.692 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
East for The Washington Post. He
talked with Jeffrey Brown at

54:21.725 --> 54:26.597 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this weekend's Miami Book Fair.
JEFFREY BROWN: Welcome to you.

54:26.630 --> 54:29.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOBY WARRICK, Author, "Black
Flags: The Rise of ISIS": Thank

54:29.199 --> 54:31.168 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
you, Jeffrey. JEFFREY BROWN:
Could not be more current, of

54:31.201 --> 54:33.170 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
course. We will get to current
events, but you are, in this

54:33.203 --> 54:35.172 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
book, looking at the backstory
of what led to today. JOBY

54:35.205 --> 54:37.174 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WARRICK: Yes. I think a lot of
people -- to a lot of people,

54:37.207 --> 54:39.743 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that ISIS seemed to come out of
nowhere last year. And the truth

54:39.776 --> 54:42.379 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is, there is a very long and
complicated story behind this

54:42.412 --> 54:44.381 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
organization. It's quite
different from al-Qaida. It's

54:44.414 --> 54:47.818 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
always been a different stripe,
but its story goes back into

54:47.851 --> 54:51.755 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
prisons in Jordan in the 1990s
and with individuals who became

54:51.788 --> 54:55.259 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
radicalized and became very
different from this message of

54:55.292 --> 54:57.861 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
al-Qaida about sort of driving
out their Western powers from

54:57.895 --> 55:00.497 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Middle East. But they wanted
to create a caliphate, this

55:00.531 --> 55:02.499 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
powerful idea. (CROSSTALK)
JEFFREY BROWN: From the

55:02.533 --> 55:04.868 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
beginning? JOBY WARRICK: From
the beginning. It was kind of

55:04.902 --> 55:07.538 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
something that morphed as they
went along, but the idea was to

55:07.571 --> 55:10.507 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
do something here and now, not
worry about far enemies, not

55:10.541 --> 55:13.277 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
worry about the Western powers,
but try to create this holy

55:13.310 --> 55:16.180 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
state, this holy empire. JEFFREY
BROWN: As with al-Qaida, it

55:16.213 --> 55:20.384 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
began, though, in jails, in
prisons, right, with a small

55:20.417 --> 55:22.619 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
core? JOBY WARRICK: Yes. That is
interesting, because a lot of

55:22.653 --> 55:25.822 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the founders of al-Qaida, as you
say, Zawahri and others, came

55:25.856 --> 55:28.358 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
out of Egyptian prisons. JEFFREY
BROWN: Egyptian prisons, right?

55:28.392 --> 55:30.527 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOBY WARRICK: Yes. JEFFREY
BROWN: Yes, also Jordan. JOBY

55:30.561 --> 55:33.430 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WARRICK: The same pedigree and
some of the same sort of beliefs

55:33.463 --> 55:35.432 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and sort of radicalization
process was fairly similar.

55:35.465 --> 55:38.035 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: A lot of
confusion and uncertainty about

55:38.068 --> 55:41.605 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
its history. A lot of confusion
about what just it is. How do

55:41.638 --> 55:44.908 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
you define ISIS? JOBY WARRICK:
Well, ISIS, you know, it's

55:44.942 --> 55:48.345 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
interesting, in that it's a
group that sort of latches on to

55:48.378 --> 55:52.449 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a few central themes that
identify it. One is this idea of

55:52.482 --> 55:55.485 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
creating the caliphate as sort
of the immediate and also

55:55.519 --> 55:58.155 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
long-term goal. This is
something they want to do. And

55:58.188 --> 56:02.492 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
there is also this embracing of
violence for its own sake. This

56:02.526 --> 56:06.029 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is not strategic violence
sometimes, but it's just to

56:06.063 --> 56:10.734 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
shock and awe or to horrify. And
they use violence and they use

56:10.767 --> 56:13.070 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
media very deliberately to
intimidate to enemies and also

56:13.103 --> 56:16.640 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to excite their base to get
other radicals to join their

56:16.673 --> 56:21.011 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
movement and to help them.
JEFFREY BROWN: So when we see

56:21.044 --> 56:24.615 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the beheadings, of course, we
see the destroying ancient

56:24.648 --> 56:27.684 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
sites, those are for effect?
JOBY WARRICK: Yes, there is a

56:27.718 --> 56:30.787 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
message there. They're not
trying to win hearts and minds

56:30.821 --> 56:33.490 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of people around the world and
not even the Muslim community.

56:33.523 --> 56:35.492 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're looking at provoking.
And that's what they're very

56:35.525 --> 56:37.494 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
good at doing. JEFFREY BROWN:
How did they get from -- the

56:37.527 --> 56:42.099 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
story you're telling is how they
got from Jordan prisons to an

56:42.132 --> 56:45.035 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
international organization. JOBY
WARRICK: Yes. JEFFREY BROWN: Was

56:45.068 --> 56:48.205 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
there a key moment along the way
when -- that you can now look

56:48.238 --> 56:51.174 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
back and say, OK, now this is
the real beginning of this

56:51.208 --> 56:53.577 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
group? JOBY WARRICK: There's a
key individual. And there's a

56:53.610 --> 56:56.546 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
terrorist whose name was Abu
Musab al Zarqawi, who was a

56:56.580 --> 57:01.652 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Jordanian terrorist, a fairly
minor figure, but he ends up

57:01.685 --> 57:06.189 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
becoming important for two
reasons. One was because the

57:06.223 --> 57:08.191 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
United States, the Bush
administration in particular,

57:08.225 --> 57:11.461 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
decided to make him kind of a
poster child for this connection

57:11.495 --> 57:14.931 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
between al-Qaida and Saddam
Hussein. They picked on some

57:14.965 --> 57:17.567 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
very flimsy evidence that
suggested a connection. And they

57:17.601 --> 57:19.703 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
actually put his picture in
front of the United Nations in

57:19.736 --> 57:23.540 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
2003 arguing for invasion of
Iraq. Turns out the evidence was

57:23.573 --> 57:25.542 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
wrong, he had nothing to do with
Saddam Hussein. He had nothing

57:25.575 --> 57:28.245 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to do really with al-Qaida, but
it was -- it made him famous. It

57:28.278 --> 57:30.881 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
gave him a platform. Suddenly,
he became an international hero

57:30.914 --> 57:33.850 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the jihadist community. And
then immediately after that, the

57:33.884 --> 57:36.987 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
invasion takes place. Zarqawi
moves into Iraq and starts this

57:37.020 --> 57:41.024 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
insurgency, which really becomes
the force that almost drove the

57:41.058 --> 57:44.428 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
U.S. to defeat in Iraq. JEFFREY
BROWN: This is part of -- a big

57:44.461 --> 57:47.898 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
part of the stories, the actions
or misactions of the U.S. and

57:47.931 --> 57:51.068 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
other Western governments. Were
those -- that kind of thing an

57:51.101 --> 57:54.338 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
act of omission or commission,
or how do you see it? JOBY

57:54.371 --> 57:56.773 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WARRICK: Yes. There's multiple
acts of commission I think in

57:56.807 --> 57:59.509 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the early days, and it was not
just the invasion itself, which

57:59.543 --> 58:03.213 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
gives people like Zarqawi a
platform and a reason to call

58:03.246 --> 58:06.583 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
others like him around the world
to help out. But also there was

58:06.616 --> 58:10.287 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a security vacuum that emerged
in Iraq in the early days, where

58:10.320 --> 58:13.390 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Baathists are disbanded, the
army is sent home. And so

58:13.423 --> 58:17.794 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Zarqawi, this fanatic, has sort
of a willing army of Iraqis

58:17.828 --> 58:20.764 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ready to help him. And,
together, they sort of blend the

58:20.797 --> 58:24.334 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
fanaticism and the military and
bureaucrat professionals ends up

58:24.368 --> 58:27.371 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
becoming this force called
al-Qaida in Iraq, and that is

58:27.404 --> 58:29.740 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the core of what is now ISIS.
It's the same group today.

58:29.773 --> 58:32.776 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And then stir in
the Syrian civil war. JOBY

58:32.809 --> 58:35.379 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WARRICK: Absolutely. So,
actually, toward the late 2000s,

58:35.412 --> 58:41.017 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Zarqawi's movement was on its
heels. Zarqawi himself was

58:41.051 --> 58:44.488 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
killed. They were kind of driven
underground. There was no real

58:44.521 --> 58:48.692 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
sense that they had any future.
Then Arab spring happens. Then

58:48.725 --> 58:51.528 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Syrian civil war takes
place. And suddenly there's a

58:51.561 --> 58:54.564 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
whole new opportunity. They
essentially get their rebirth in

58:54.598 --> 58:58.468 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the ashes of the Syrian state.
JEFFREY BROWN: One of the key

58:58.502 --> 59:02.906 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
questions now, of course, is how
organized is ISIS? Who is -- is

59:02.939 --> 59:06.643 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it centrally run or are these
cells out there? JOBY WARRICK:

59:06.676 --> 59:09.713 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Well, they do have this powerful
central organization. It's

59:09.746 --> 59:13.817 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
remarkable to me to see how good
they are at things like

59:13.850 --> 59:17.220 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
logistics, how good they are at
getting supplies and moving

59:17.254 --> 59:20.290 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
recruits to various places,
getting suicide bombers to take

59:20.323 --> 59:23.927 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on these incredible missions.
But, also, they are very good at

59:23.960 --> 59:26.663 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
inspiring people in other parts
of the world to kind of take up

59:26.696 --> 59:29.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the same mantle. And we don't
always know how well-connected

59:29.900 --> 59:33.603 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
some of the local groups are to
ISIS central. There is clearly

59:33.637 --> 59:36.373 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
at least some messaging through
propaganda and some actual

59:36.406 --> 59:38.408 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
coordination as well. JEFFREY
BROWN: Messaging through

59:38.442 --> 59:40.811 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
propaganda? JOBY WARRICK: Yes.
So, ISIS -- for example, this

59:40.844 --> 59:45.048 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
recent Paris attack, so this
individual Abdelhamid Abaaoud in

59:45.081 --> 59:47.651 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Paris, who is the ringleader of
the attack, he gets sort of

59:47.684 --> 59:51.788 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
chided publicly by ISIS'
propaganda ministers in Syria,

59:51.822 --> 59:55.225 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
saying, do something in Paris,
these Westerners have to pay for

59:55.258 --> 59:57.661 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the things they're doing do us.
And so that becomes, we think,

59:57.694 --> 01:00:01.031 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
part of what drove him to commit
this crime. JEFFREY BROWN: You

01:00:01.064 --> 01:00:03.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
used the word chided. That's an
interesting... JOBY WARRICK:

01:00:03.066 --> 01:00:05.035 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Yes. There was this... JEFFREY
BROWN: It's not order. It's not

01:00:05.068 --> 01:00:08.305 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
like could you -- why don't you
-- chiding? JOBY WARRICK: Yes.

01:00:08.338 --> 01:00:10.307 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There may be some of that too.
But it feels like there is

